cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. 

The paper proposes a novel bidirectional recurrent neural network (BRNN) model for question answering (QA) tasks, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The factoid QA task involves retrieving information from a large corpus of text, which could also place the paper under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the proposed model involves putting supervision at every time step, which could suggest the involvement of reinforcement learning techniques, placing the paper under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
